The service in both the casual restaurant at breakfast and the dining room in the evening was efficient.	The restaurant also had good food (we were given a $10 per person coupon to use in the restaurant from the hotel).	We had dinner in the attached restaurant, and the food was absolutely delicious.	There were elevators, gift shop, restaurant and lots of other dining choices just across the street.	The hotel restaurant was nice enough, but again, bland; the food was nicely presented but had no taste.	The breakfast in the restaurant was amazing, and the staff was very attentive and friendly.